	<div align="justify">
<p>
Try to find the answer of the following questions by yourself
<br>
<ol>
	<li>Why is the hydrolysis of cane sugar considered a first order reaction?</li>
	<li>What is the difference between order and molecularity of a reaction?</li>
	
	<li>What is <b>optical rotation</b>?</li>
		<li>What is <b>chirality</b>?</li>
		<li>Do you expect any trouble if the optically active reactant is dissolved in an optically active solvent?</li>
		<li>How does the concentration of H+ ion affect the reaction rate?</li>
		</ol></div>
	

